## First-time Setup

After cloning the repo, run:
```bash
make setup
```
This installs the pre-commit hook that reminds you to update AI memory when committing.

## Instructions for AI Agent

After completing every task:
1. Update or create `.project-memory/tasks/active/[your-name]-[task-slug].md`
2. If task is done → append one-line summary to `.project-memory/tasks/done.md`, delete active file
3. If there are architecture changes → update `.project-memory/memory/architecture.md`
4. If there are new modules → update `.project-memory/memory/modules.md`
5. Commit all `.project-memory/` changes together with the code

Active task file naming: `[developer-name]-[task-slug].md`
Examples: `alice-order-refactor.md`, `bob-payment-v2.md`

